            <p>To evaluate the performance of our word sense disambiguation system, we used CHJ-WLSP as both training and validation data, with the Corpus of Historical Japanese (CHJ) as our target corpus.</p>
            <p>
                <hi rend="color(222222)" style="font-size:10pt">Additionally, we incorporated BCCWJ-WLSP (Maekawa et al. 2014) for supplementary training data. BCCWJ-WLSP is a sense-tagged corpus derived from the Balanced Corpus of Contemporary Japanese (BCCWJ) [8], which provides a comprehensive resource of contemporary Japanese usage. Table 4 presents a summary of the statistics for CHJ-WLSP, as derived and calculated from (Maekawa et al. 2014).</hi>
            </p>
            <p style="text-align: center;">Table 4. Statistics of BCCWJ-WLSP</p>
            <table rend="rules">
                <row>
                    <cell style="text-align: left;">Tokens</cell>
                    <cell style="text-align: right;">182,166</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell style="text-align: left;">Types</cell>
                    <cell style="text-align: right;">20,010</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
