            <p style="text-align: left;">
                <hi rend="color(222222)" style="font-size:10pt" xml:space="preserve">Table 6 lists the three most frequently tagged word senses within CHJ. Concept IDs 2.3430 and 2.12000 correspond to verbs such as </hi>
                <hi rend="italic color(222222)" style="font-family:Arial Unicode MS;font-size:10pt"><hi rend="Japanese">する</hi></hi>
                <hi rend="color(222222)" style="font-size:10pt" xml:space="preserve"> (suru, "do") and </hi>
                <hi rend="italic color(222222)" style="font-family:Arial Unicode MS;font-size:10pt"><hi rend="Japanese">ございます</hi></hi>
                <hi rend="color(222222)" style="font-size:10pt" xml:space="preserve"> (gozaimasu, "be"), which are also prevalent in BCCWJ. Conversely, Concept ID 1.2301, which represents terms for people, appears less frequently in BCCWJ. We plan to make CHJ accessible via a web-based search system that allows queries based on word meanings.</hi>
            </p>
